task.summary: Removing package-lock to let users choose their versions of react & angular
Attempt to work around debug mode (#1) by hacking ngReact into providing us with the scope
Add a HOC to inject the scope in custom directives
Verify that setting scope in ngReact directives works
Fix: do not fail if the ngReact module is not defined
Fix: expose the HOC and the directive link decorator

Change the way we decorate ngReact, as we really can't count on the loading order to be OK.
Add a lot of warnings.
